main event: Radar contacts with an unidentified airborne object reported on November 10, 1950, over South Ruislip, England.
interesting points: Multiple radar contacts showed an unidentified object moving erratically at high speeds., The object reached an altitude of approximately 25,000 feet and was tracked over 1-3 minutes., One contact was made within close proximity to a B-29 aircraft., The object reportedly executed maneuvers that seemed to defy the laws of physics., No visual contact with the object was made during the sighting.
sighted object: unidentified airborne object tracked by radar
witness description: Reports were based on radar observations from U.S. Air Force personnel.
